OL,3,COutgoing police chief facing
OL,4,Cmisconduct investigation
OL,6,F"We will now conduct a thorough
OL,7,Finvestigation, independently of the
OL,8,Fpolice, into the matters brought to
OL,9,Four attention."
OL,11,FMr Evison said he had received details
OL,12,Fof "potential misconduct relating to
OL,13,Fthe chief constable" on Monday 12 June.
OL,15,FHe said: "Following further enquiries
OL,16,Fand due consideration it became
OL,17,Fapparent that the OPCC was obliged to
OL,18,Frefer the matter to the IOPC and this
OL,19,Fwas done on Monday 24 June.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/7
